到達目標:
By the end of the
course, learners will be better able to:

&nbsp;

*speak more fluently
on selected topics and tasks through regular small and large scale
presentations; 

*use a range of
interaction strategies and relevant language to communicate effectively in
group work and discussions;

*exchange opinions on
a range of issues;&nbsp; 

*present ideas using a
coherent structure, appropriate connecting language, and paralinguistic skills
(e.g. eye contact, posture/gestures) for individual presentations; 

*use visual aids (e.g.
poster/ppt) to effectively support presentation content;

*understand English
spoken in a range of accents from around the world;

* understand and use
topic-specific and general, mid-frequency vocabulary items. 

*read fluently,
through regular extensive-reading practice.
